items.title: IPO-bound Pine Labs turns profitable in June quarter of FY26
items.description: Online payments firm Pine Labs has achieved its first quarterly net profit in the June quarter of FY26. This milestone follows strong operating revenue growth. The company is now preparing for its Initial Public Offering. Pine Labs plans to raise funds through fresh share issuance and an offer for sale. The firm is targeting a significant valuation.

items.title: Titan Q2 Preview: Profit may surge 38% YoY; jewellery growth seen moderating amid high gold prices3.
items.description: Titan Company is projected to post a 38% year-on-year rise in Q2 FY26 profit, supported by steady core business growth and a low base effect. While high gold prices and delayed festive demand may slow jewellery sales, brokerages remain optimistic about Titan’s long-term growth and margin stability.
